### Microservices Swagger Endpoints
### Open these URLs in your browser after running the services

### ============================================
### SWAGGER UI ENDPOINTS
### ============================================

### Product Service Swagger
# Open: https://localhost:7001/swagger

### Payment Service Swagger  
# Open: https://localhost:7002/swagger

### Order Service Swagger
# Open: https://localhost:7000/swagger

### API Gateway (No Swagger - uses Ocelot)
# Open: https://localhost:7100

### ============================================
### QUICK API TESTS (via API Gateway)
### ============================================

@gateway = https://localhost:7100

### 1. Get All Products (via Gateway)
GET {{gateway}}/products
Accept: application/json

###

### 2. Get All Orders (via Gateway)
GET {{gateway}}/orders
Accept: application/json

###

### 3. Get All Payments (via Gateway)
GET {{gateway}}/payments
Accept: application/json

###

### ============================================
### DIRECT SERVICE TESTS
### ============================================

@productService = https://localhost:7001
@orderService = https://localhost:7000
@paymentService = https://localhost:7002

### Get Products (Direct)
GET {{productService}}/api/products
Accept: application/json

###

### Get Orders (Direct)
GET {{orderService}}/api/orders
Accept: application/json

###

### Get Payments (Direct)
GET {{paymentService}}/api/payments
Accept: application/json

###

### ============================================
### CREATE PRODUCT
### ============================================

### Create a Product
POST {{productService}}/api/products
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Laptop",
  "description": "High-performance laptop",
  "price": 999.99,
  "stock": 50,
  "category": "Electronics"
}

###

### ============================================
### CREATE ORDER (Saga Orchestration)
### ============================================

### Create an Order (This triggers the Saga)
POST {{orderService}}/api/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "productId": 1,
  "quantity": 2,
  "paymentMethod": "CreditCard"
}

###
